<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Amber" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Amber,</orth> a fossil resin: <bibl n="shak. lc 37" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.87" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 87</bibl>. Resin in general: <cit><quote>thick a. and plum-tree gum,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.201" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 201</bibl></cit>.<lb />Adjectively: <bibl n="shak. pp 366" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 366</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.87" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.224" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 224</bibl> (placed after the subst. in a popular rhyme).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>